h_{TT}\COVARIANTINDEX{\alpha\beta} & =h_{TT}\COVARIANTINDEX{\alpha\beta}\PARENTHESES{t-\frac{z}{c}}\\
 & =h_{+}e_{+}\COVARIANTINDEX{\alpha\beta}+h_{\times}e_{\times}\COVARIANTINDEX{\alpha\beta}
\end{align*}

\end_inset

 is a wave propagating in the 
\begin_inset Formula $z$
\end_inset

 direction and 
\begin_inset Formula $h_{TT}$
\end_inset

 I think it means 
\begin_inset Formula $h_{\text{Transverse-Traceless}}$
\end_inset

, but not sure.
 Thus 
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
T^{\text{GW}}\COVARIANTINDEX{00}=\frac{c^{4}}{16\pi G}\ANGLEBRACKETS{\dot{h}_{+}^{2}+\dot{h}_{\times}^{2}}
\]

\end_inset

 
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
-cT\COVARIANTINDEX{03}=-cT\COVARIANTINDEX{30}=c^{2}T\COVARIANTINDEX{33}=T^{\text{GW}}\COVARIANTINDEX{00}
\]

\end_inset

 and all other components are zero.
 (We used that 
\begin_inset Formula $e_{+}\CONTRAVARIANTINDEX{ij}e_{\times}\COVARIANTINDEX{ij}=e_{\times}\CONTRAVARIANTINDEX{ij}e_{+}\COVARIANTINDEX{ij}=2$
