 We are interested in solving the Einstein field equations for this 
\begin_inset Formula $T$
\end_inset

.
 Me limito a una tarea de copista de ahora en adelante, sin interpretaci√≥n.
 
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
h_{ij,j}=0\rightarrow\boxed{\tau\CONTRAVARIANTINDEX{ij}\COVARIANTINDEX{ij}=0}\text{ conservation law for coordinate system}
\]

\end_inset

 
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\square\bar{h}\COVARIANTINDEX{ij}\PARENTHESES{t,\VECTOR x}=\frac{4G}{c^{4}}\intop\frac{\tau_{ik}\PARENTHESES{t-\frac{\MODULE{\VECTOR x-\VECTOR x\PRIME}}{c},\VECTOR x\PRIME}}{\MODULE{\VECTOR x-\VECTOR x\PRIME}}\DIFERENTIAL^{3}x\PRIME
\]

\end_inset

This is the integral we have to solve.
 We will solve this in two regimes:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Far-zone: Means that 
\begin_inset Formula $R\ll\lambda\ll r$
\end_inset

 where 
\begin_inset Formula $R$
\end_inset

 is the source size and 
\begin_inset Formula $r$
\end_inset

 the distance we are looking from.
